</td></table></center></td></table></center>


</td></tr><tr><td colspan=2>



<p><br>

The Javan (or Lesser One-horned) Rhinoceros is considered to be the rarest large mammal species in the world. The
       rhino is a dusky grey colour with a single horn; the skin has a number of loose folds giving the appearance of armour
       plating. This species is very similar in appearance to the closely related Great Indian Rhinoceros, but is slightly smaller,
       with a much smaller head and less developed folds of skin on the neck. . . .

<p>

<img src="graphics/line2.gif" alt="line">

