<TITLE>WWF News 1995 - Members Only</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<body background="/graphics/back.gif" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="ff0000"><br>
<center>
<img src="NEWShead2.gif" alt="WWF News Winter 1995"></center><p>
<P>
<p>
<blockquote><blockquote><p>Dear WWF friends,<p>
For 35 years WWF has relied on individuals like you who have donated
money and time to help protect the environment. WWF could not
survive without your help.<p>
        With an international network of almost five million supporters,
<img src="membersonlygrph.jpg" alt="Picture of Member's Only logo" align=right>

there is reason for WWF to be optimistic about the future, even
though we need to redouble fundraising efforts to continue the
fight. These supporters know they can rely on WWF to offer practical
solutions to environmental problems through field projects run
by cutting-edge experts and effective lobbying of governments
all over the world.<p>
        A WWF membership puts you on the conservation frontline.
It is generosity that has enabled WWF to create, for example,
a marine park in Tanzania, the southern ocean whale sanctuary,
a conservation training centre in Thailand, and new campaigns
on climate change, fisheries, and forests. Specific solutions
to specific problems. It's the WWF way.<p>
     WWF thanks you for the last 35 years of accomplishment. But
we still need your help as we approach the next century.<p>
        Of those who are not yet members we ask: do you care enough
to join 4.7 million people around the world to leave a better
planet for the next generation? The first step is an easy one.
Just fax or post the form below and we'll be in touch. There is
still much work to be done.<p>
<p>
Best wishes,<p>

<p>
Deborah Denhardt<BR>
Membership Services Manager<p>


</blockquote></blockquote><center><br clear=all>
