<HEAD>

<TITLE>Untitled</TITLE>


<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>
<body background="/graphics/back.gif"  bgcolor="#ffffff"  vlink="#ff0000"   text="#000000" link="ff0000">

<br><center><img src="NEWShead.gif" alt="WWF News Winter 1995"><p>

<br><img src="35YEARSHD2.GIF" alt="35 Years of WWF Achievement"></center><p>


<blockquote><blockquote><img src="sinitialgrph.gif" align=left>ince WWF's first project - 
a US$130,000 grant to its then scientific partner IUCN-The World 
Conservation Union - more than 10,000 have followed. The WWF 
network now works in 96 countries.
<p>
        With such an wide-reaching programme, the number of things
the organization is proud of having accomplished or been a part
of could easily fill a book. So <I>WWF News</I> has put together
highlights and &quot;top 10&quot; lists of the organization's
achievements over the last 35 years. <p>
        What quickly becomes apparent is how all the projects
and actions, no matter how different, are related. Change the
way countries calculate their gross domestic product, and it can
ease the threats to forests, which in turn protects wildlife.
Raise awareness of a certain species, and it's easier to save
the forest where it lives. Conservation is not linear: like nature
it is a complex web.<a href="achievesty2.htm">CONTINUED.</a></blockquote><p>
<CENTER><img src="BARGRPH2.gif"></CENTER<P>

