<html>

<head>

<title> WWF Netherlands-Our Philosophy </title>

</head>

<body background="graphics/bg1.gif" link="#ffffff" vlink="#ffffff" alink="#ff0000">

<table  width=85% border=0>

<tr><td width=125 valign=top>
<center>
<img src="graphics/wwflogo4.gif" alt="wwf logo"><p>
</center>
<br>
<font size=2>
<a href="profile.htm"><b>Profile</b></a><p>
<a href="philosophy.htm"><b>Our Philosophy</b></a><p>
<a href="strategic.htm"><b>Strategic Alliances</b></a><p>
<a href="priorities.htm"><b>WWF-Netherlands' Priorities</b></a><p>
<a href="innovate.htm"><b>Innovative Ideas</b></a><p>
</font>
</td>

<td width=30><br>&nbsp;</td>
<td width=465 valign=middle>
<img src="graphics/philosophyhd2.gif" alt="Our Philosophy">
<p>
<br>
<img src="graphics/philosophyimg.jpg" align=right alt="coastline at sunset">

WWF cannot save the world's nature alone. Our task is to convince people of the importance of saving nature. Therefore many 
WWF projects are model-projects which show others how to protect nature effectively.
<p>
WWF is also known as an organization which creates a structure in many projects all over the world, which enable them to 
eventually become independent of WWF support. Realizing their importance to the success of an initiative, WWF also now 
prefers to cooperate with local people in the execution of projects. 


 <br> <br> <br>

