<html>

<head>

<title> WWF Netherlands-Strategic Alliances </title>

</head>

<body background="graphics/bg1.gif" link="#ffffff" vlink="#ffffff" alink="#ff0000">

<table  width=85% border=0>

<tr><td width=125 valign=top>
<center>
<img src="graphics/wwflogo4.gif" alt="wwf logo"><p>
</center>
<br>
<font size=2>
<a href="profile.htm"><b>Profile</b></a><p>
<a href="philosophy.htm"><b>Our Philosophy</b></a><p>
<a href="strategic.htm"><b>Strategic Alliances</b></a><p>
<a href="priorities.htm"><b>WWF-Netherlands' Priorities</b></a><p>
<a href="innovate.htm"><b>Innovative Ideas</b></a><p>
</font>
</td>

<td width=30><br>&nbsp;</td>
<td width=465 valign=middle>
<img src="graphics/strategichd2.gif" alt="Strategic Alliances">
<p>
<br>
<img src="graphics/strategicimg.jpg" align=right alt="office buildings">

The World Wide Fund for Nature strives to have strategic alliances with various elements in society, politics, government, 
the business world and non-profit organizations. The aim is to create mutually beneficial situations, and to rearrange 
production and  consumption processes in a way benefiting both nature and the economy. 
<p>
Work should not duplicate other existing efforts, and must really  be of use. It should be within WWF's organisational 
capacities, or in partnership with other organizations. Six programmes have been outlined along these lines. They form the 
basis for WWF-Netherlands's management policy.


 <br> <br> <br>

