<img src="hd7.gif" alt="Panda Quest"></center><p>
<BR>
<blockquote><blockquote>
<img src="wingerphoto.jpg" alt="Picture of a panda" align=right>
In search of a wild panda, actress Debra Winger (<I>Officer and
a Gentleman, Terms of Endearment</I>) hooks up with China's premier
panda expert, Professor Pan Wenshi - &quot;the one man who holds
the key to finding the elusive animal&quot; - in a new programme
that is part of London-based Meridien Broadcasting's award-winning
&quot;In the Wild&quot; series.<p>
       Winger, along with her son Noah, goes from the streets
of Shanghai to the China Conservation and Research Centre for
the Giant Panda in Wolong, and finally to the remote Qinling Mountains
where Professor Pan has been studying wild pandas for 12 years.
That's where they get lucky. Along the way Winger learns about
the threats the less than 1,000 remaining wild pandas face. WWF
funds Professor Pan's work through project <I>CN0005.3: Support
to Chinese Scientists. LG</I></blockquote></blockquote><p>
<p>

