<HEAD>

<TITLE>Untitled-27</TITLE>

<!-- Date: Wednesday, June 5, 1996  11:59 AM -->

</HEAD>



<body background="/graphics/back.gif" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="ff0000"><br>
<center>



<IMG SRC="images/heading.gif"  WIDTH=197 HEIGHT=81 ALIGN=TOP></center><BR>

<center> <hr size=1 width=300 no shade></center>
<center>

<center>
<H2><font color="ff0000">The ceremony</font></H2>
<table><tr><td width=350>


Kaya Gandini is an oasis of dense greenery amidst the semi-arid, degraded terrain of the Kinango area behind the Shimba Hills of Kwale District, southwest of Mombasa. Here, though the Duruma people struggle to eke out a living from the parched soils, grow
ing crops such as maize, cassava, and finger millet, their Kaya remains intact because they strongly respect the sacred rules.

	At 6AM, a group of 20 elders, which includes women, barefoot and draped in navy blue cloths, congregates at the sacred spot Chizia cha Nyere, where a small cone-shaped hut of swamp grass and poles from a special tree stands under a baobab outside the Kay
a. This is the shelter for the vitsimbakazi, the sprits which must be appeased before the rains can fall and an "ill wind" believed to bring diseases such as malaria and chicken pox chased away. The elders place cakes of ground maize on a shelf for the vi
tsimbakazi. And on the ground they lay a bowl of water and some leaves to clean the air and medicinal herbs for peace. 

	The group dances, sings, and calls the spirits. Then the Mwanatsi, or spiritual leader, leads a procession to a series of sacred sites where similar rituals are carried out. At each spot, the Mwanatsi chants incantations and leaves behind a black hen.

	In the afternoon the ceremony moves inside the Kaya. The elders pray for peace, and this time a new Mwanatsi is annointed. Only a select few "outsiders" are allowed to witness this part of the ritual. A sheep and black bull are slaughtered, cooked, and e
aten in the forest. The Duruma believe that if performed properly, rain will fall. It rained the next day.
</td></center>
</tr></table></center>

<BR>
<center>
<IMG SRC="images/panda.gif"  WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=89 ALIGN=TOP>
</center>

<BR>
<center>
<a href="/graphics/toolbar.map"><img src="/graphics/toolbar.gif" border=0 ISMAP></a>
<center>
