<P>
<P>
<H2>CD-ROM, bilingual English and French, on international humanitarian law (&quot;IHL&quot;)</H2>
<P><I></I>
<P>
<P><B>You will quickly be able to:</B><BR>

<P>- find a text or a specific article of a treaty;<BR>

<P>- check which States have signed, ratified or acceded or succeeded to a convention;<BR>

<P>- scan the texts and match a given provision with the corresponding commentary. etc.<BR>

<P><B>What does the IHL CD-ROM comprise?</B><BR>

<P>- some 87 treaties and other texts: Law of the Hague, Law of Geneva and other IHL treaties dating from 1856 to the present;<BR>

<P>- the commentaries published by the ICRC on the four Geneva Conventions of 1949 and their 1977 Additional Protocols;<BR>

<P>- an up-to-date list of signatures, ratifications, accessions and successions relating to IHL treaties, as well as the full text of reservations, declarations and objections thereto (as at 31 December 1994).<BR>

<P>
<TABLE border>
<TR valign=top><TD>
<P>To use CR-ROM IHL, you need :<BR>

<P>* IBM PC, XT, AT, PS/2 or compatible, with 640 K RAM and hard;<BR>

<P>* Black and white monitor or colour monitor with VGA graphic card;<BR>

<P>* MS-DOS 3.1, or higher;<BR>

<P>* Standard CD-ROM drive (ISO 9660)</TD></TR></TABLE>
<BR>

